	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Sep 18th 6:43 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Good day to you my fellow bard.<br><br>Well last night was a happy one indeed.  After chain fearing an Aviak harrier to the grave ;), I heard a little ding and was finally able to pull out and memorize Solons Song of the Sirens (our first charm).  I'm sure it had been burning a hole in my backpack :) <br><br>I had heard more that a few rumors that this little song definitely had its uses, but its effectiveness had been reduced so that, for example, we could no longer charm and kill solo Froon and Choon (lvl 30) at a time when they are still red to me.<br><br>So what did I do???  Being the (generally dumb) unbeliever I am I ran as fast as I could to Choon and Froon of course!  Fully expecting to fail, but yet I stood before those damn big fellows and played my new little song with mino horn in hand - charm landed successfully!  And again.  And again.... in the end I killed each five times last night just for the utter joy of it :) (and to test whether it was just a fluke) - well after from getting my runes for lambent.  Two out of three charms landed successfully throughout.  Not too shabby at all....<br><br>The only tough part was kiting the winner of the fight between them!  Running in large cirles definitely works best as the difference between the max range of bellow and when they can whack ya one is very small unfortunately - and this is the easiest way to keep the range just perfect IMHO.<br><br>BTW the technique.  Simple, <br>charm one, <br>/pet attack the other, <br>re selo yourself, <br>stand near max range of charm,<br>When charm wears off recharm,<br>re selo,<br>etc etc,<br>when they are near death charm the stronger,<br>kill weaker mob,<br>kite last little bit of health from the winner with bellow....<br><br>My conclusion - not earth shattering but hey it has to be said!  <br>(A)This song works, and I mean in a 'like wow' way.  I still want to test some more but so far so good.  Why?  See (B)<br><br>(B)I have high CHA for a lvl 27 bard (125ish).  It matters, don't neglect it as in my opinion it is as important as DEX is for a bard... AC being most important.  Get some electrum (+7cha +5dex) or gold (+5cha +7dex) star ruby rings.  Kill gnasher, do the quest and get a medal of merit (+5 cha) or just use a Griffenne charm (+3cha +3ac).  Also get a mino horn.  Minos are easy to kill past mid-teens and some sites say they increase the effectiveness of wind songs... even if it doesn't there is no hurt in having one as it is lighter than a flute.<br><br>Hope this was interesting to ye and Best of luck :)<br><br>Ayre<br>Wee surfer bard of Terris-Thule<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
